    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-29T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-29T11:00:00-05:00" n="171"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d171">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 124.511/24</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HMT1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-29T11:00:00-05:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">August 29, 1914, 11 a.m.</hi>
                    </date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>Your August 27, 12 midnight. In the event of the seat of government being moved,
                    the Department will be guided by your judgment as to whether the Embassy should
                    remain in Paris or follow the Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
